items.title: How Tiffany Trump’s Husband Benefited From Proximity to Power
items.description: A Times investigation found that Michael Boulos and his family benefited financially from proximity to his in-laws for years.

items.title: Wisconsin Woman Who Flew to UK to Try to Kill a Man Gets 30-Year Sentence
items.description: Aimee Betro, 45, was convicted this month of attempting to shoot a man near Birmingham, England, in 2019.

items.title: Zelensky, Back From Washington, Projects More Confidence in Peace Talks
items.description: The Ukrainian leader returned with a U.S. commitment to participate in security guarantees for Kyiv in a postwar settlement.

items.title: Women in Indian Sports Sweat for Their Share of a Booming Market
items.description: Female athletes are using social media to increase viewership and seek better sponsorship deals in a field long dominated by men.

items.title: Brazil-U.S. Talks on Mining Rare Earth Minerals Are Complicated by Trump’s Tariffs
items.description: Tensions between President Trump and Brazil’s leader could derail a promising alliance to unlock the world’s second largest reserve of the minerals.
